<h2>Conference Travel for Dummies</h2>

<h3>Applying for financial grant</h3>
<h4>Required letters:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Cover letter to Dean AR</li>
<li>DC recommendation letter</li>
<li>Institute financial grant template</li>
<li>Bona fide request letter to DR</li>
</ul>

<h4>Enclosures:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Conference acceptance letter (email and/or webpage print)</li>
<li>Abstract of your paper</li>
<li>Grade sheet</li>
<li>Comprehensive completion letter</li>
<li>Accommodation details (print of hotel webpage with price, e.g.\ booking.com)</li>
<li>Visa fee (print of webpage)</li>
<li>Air India quotation</li>
</ul>

<h4>Plan:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Go to Air India office and submit the quotation request. You may be asked to come after two or three days to collect.</li>
<li>Send mails to DC members and get appoinments for signatures on DC reco letter.</li>
<li>Go to Acad section (4th floor), and submite gradesheet request. If lucky, you may be given the gradesheet immediately.</li>
<li>If compre letter is not with you, go to dept office and ask them to give you a copy of it. It will be present in your file.</li>
<li>Check visa vfsglobal website for fees.</li>
<li>Check booking.com website for stay price.</li>
<li>Request an amount greater than 1.5 lakhs so that they would give 1.5 lakhs, else you might get lesser.</li>
</ul>

